Daily menu of an obese child: not breakfast and dinner stuffed
Over one third of children aged between 9 and 13 years have overweight problems, where overweight affects 9 per cent of the school population and obesity at 5%.
Most obese children come from families with an unhealthy lifestyle, according to current research.
It again demonstrates the importance of the environment where it grows for a healthy development of the person, as well as the models that serve as a reference.
At the table, obsessive children are fed, for example, of sausages at least twice as often as children of families with normal weight.
For dinner, more than 19% of obese people had eaten fries the day before the analysis, which is linked to the prevention program " Obesity is not a coincidence."
In families of overweight children, there is no custom to practice sports, which applies to most current families, where only 15 per cent of children responded that their parents, at least once a week, find time for physical exercise.
Survey of 900 children
The survey was conducted at the end of last school year and participated in the same nearly 900 children of Basic Education throughout the Czech Republic.
It was already the second edition of the program of "The Obesity of Not a Chance", which supports the General Health Insurance Company and Unilever.
So far, more than 12,000 children have participated in the project from the 4th to the 8th course.
An adequate diet and adequate exercise in the family are determining factors, which significantly decrease the number of children with overweight and even obesity.
"Only half of the children surveyed have responded that they have five daily meals according to the regime: breakfast, lunch, food, snack and dinner, which is one of the basic conditions for a healthy diet," she collects one of the survey results.
No breakfast but with sausage for dinner
Experts warn that, in healthy development, details are also important, which also count, such as having a fixed hour for family breakfast.
In Czechia, however, only 23 per cent of schoolchildren's families breakfast at the same time.
In most families, each one has breakfast alone.
But the worst thing was to find out that 10% of households don't have breakfast.
Breakfast is, however, the basis of a correct daily diet.
The study shows that in families of obese children, healthy fries are consumed more frequently.
Almost all - regardless of weight - drink daily sweet refreshments (70%).
In general, more than 40 per cent of children surveyed do sports, but among their parents, this result is reduced to less than half, only 15 per cent.
Make your diet
The next phase of the study enabled the chosen boys (204 boys and 172 girls from 13 schools) to create their own diets from all possible offers according to their tastes and opinions.
"The food preferences of Czech children between 12 and 15 years of age, from the point of view of a healthy diet, are far from ideal."
Among their favorite foods are pasta, meat and sweets
"It is especially alarming the popularity of sweet refreshments," is announced in the final report of the study.
As main food the palm is taken the paste and closely follows the poultry meat.
Practically, children always reject vegetables and taste for fish and vegetables is very low.
Switching to healthy habits
At the same time, the study shows that children are willing to change their eating habits if they receive fair information.
"In the control group of the study participants, who filled out the questionnaire after the completion of the prevention programme " Obesity is not a coincidence", a significant change was given in many cases in favour of the principles of healthy eating," the results of the study point out.
Call attention, for example, to sweet refreshments, where many children would begin to prefer normal and running water.
Children would also more frequently choose poultry meat and fish for main food in the questionnaire and restrict the consumption of sweet food and flour derivatives.
