In Need for Speed: The Run competes all over America.
Review
A journey, in principle unoccupied, is complicated because of a series of unwarranted neglects of a routine journey during the morning shift.
To some extent, expectations were met, but that is of no use, if, in reality, nothing extraordinary was meant to be done.
The new delivery, to which The Run is added, aroused great expectations before its premiere.
I promised I'd blow up the old racing saga Need for Speed and, after the show, it appears like a game that shouldn't end up being a genre of action without more.
We are also curious to know how the scenes inserted would look, where the main character comes down from the car and walks through his own foot.
As is usually the case in the NFS series, the results do not vary much in terms of what we expected.
There are races that can be taken as acceptable, but in total computing points are lost due to absurd errors, which have been appearing in the series for years.
It is not actually possible or called errors, but rather the incomprehensible disengagement of programmers.
The adventure starts very well.
You are introduced into a story, whose protagonist, Jack, has certain personal problems; to solve them, you are offered to participate in an illegal race throughout America.
You sit at the wheel on the west coast of San Francisco, and your mission is to get to New York first.
The idea is to offer something interesting.
The route is divided into ten stages and then into more than fifty races.
It follows that each race takes place on a different route and the stages are located in different environments, which are quite diverse and interesting.
Thus, one does not even remotely feel that the game always offers the same thing.
Some of the environments are even pleasant in sight, although the technical level of the graph is equivalent to that of previous deliveries of the series.
Therefore, it is nothing of the other world.
But the walk through the desert, the autumn landscape or the high snowcapped mountains produce a very pleasant visual effect.
In addition, races are diversified from time to time by an atypical element.
So, for example, in the desert you find a sandstorm that decreases visibility.
On the other hand, in the mountains you must be careful not to bury a flood.
According to that, each of the races is well developed.
There are only a couple of models, but that's enough.
For a moment, you try to advance a number of required rivals (the normal one in a classic race), then try to earn time (the classic timed duel) and then expect a duel against a single opponent.
In the middle of all this sometimes comes the police, which only makes things even harder.
The novelty is the landscapes outside the car.
Interactive animations are presented when Jack, in most cases, has to escape someone and you have to help him, always pressing the right button at the right time.
Nothing complicated.
It is surprising, however, that there are far fewer landscapes in the game than could be expected (in particular there are only three).
But the final result is positive, because this element does not become annoying and, in the context already mentioned, it is one of the elements that make the game more interesting.
The driving model follows the footprints of previous episodes.
That means it's no longer a big deal today, but it can't be said to be bad.
If you're looking for a realistic simulation, you can look elsewhere.
But a race designed with a lot of action suits this style of driving, although we can find something better between the games of competition.
So far, everything's in order.
But problems arise after a certain time.
Unlike the correct driving models, this is no longer the case with collisions.
Of games of this type you can't expect it to create deformations and complicated collisions, but in fact before a blow against any object, you can't predict how your car will react, with which not everything is in order.
It is typical that, by making a very tight advance or circulating the car with a normal traffic, there are only slight rocks, but in other almost identical situations, your car ends up making uncontrolled pirouettes.
Or even ends completely destroyed.
Thanks to the reset system, there are no big problems, but it can put you in a bad mood.
The resets are programmed in such a way that, when you suffer an accident or get off the track, the game returns you to the last point of rescue on the track.
However, only five resets are available in each race.
If you consume them all, you have to restart the race from the beginning.
So it's just a help in case something's not going well, but it's not much to trust.
Sometimes, neither the reset helps, only helps to learn the given stage of memory.
A great disadvantage of the game is that the same facts are repeated in different places.
In some curves, for example, you must enter in a specific way; otherwise, they are impossible to take.
Other times you find yourself somewhere "civil" vehicles always with the same configuration, although you are the first, fifth or you arrived five minutes before or after.
This makes you angry above all in situations, when you see that two cars going to meet in opposite directions, your opponent makes no trouble, but when you get there, you have to either turn or slow down.
It is the same when you arrive, because it is programmed that the "surprise" will always happen before your noses.
Opponents also have one more advantage.
During the whole game you will reach places where, regardless of the moment, the same opponent will always advance you in the same place.
This also happens at the end of the game, on a long bridge, which is even more shocking.
Your opponent must arrive before you, at any price.
When it goes ahead of you, it makes it difficult for you to see the cars that come in front of you, so at first you can pry the car.
You can understand the idea of creating a game with maximum doses of suspension and adrenaline, but execution is so apparent that you are sure to be disappointed right away.
And it's a shame, because although the model of the trip is simple, the game is fun and with action, so it's often not possible to follow the detail what happens or where.
And it really doesn't matter, if merit takes the idea with fifty exclusive tracks or the classification in the race so that it doesn't stop boredom, or anything else.
An unusual idea is the change of cars during the races.
You have to be aware of the gas pumps next to the road, because right there you have to switch cars, although in the vast majority of cases you will need what you have.
The cars are divided into three categories.
Sports are suitable for urban areas, American strong cars for straight highways and super-sport exotics for technical driving, for example by mountain roads with curves.
In addition, the main narrative thread also appears a thread of parallel challenges, that is, there are races in specific places that you will know for stories.
Here you will get not only medals, but also points of experience for your profile, which serves both challenges and stories.
At the top level, the driver opens several possibilities, starting with the car and ending with profile funds.
At the same time, an online Autolog function is connected, which compares your results with those of other players and provides other community functions.
One of the most difficult elements to understand is how the last race in history is made.
With the car you reach the subway tunnel (step), where you start running in the dark along the tracks (step).
The speed meter marks you between 150 and 200 km/h (pass) and, suddenly, behind you comes the subway convoy and you are taken in front of you without further.
In the editorial we will certainly have a discussion about this for several days, about whether during the programming of the game none thought even a little or whether the authors really take us for a bunch of fools.
The technical part of the game is nothing extraordinary, but at least the general visual effects result in most pleasant cases, sometimes even superb.
What a pity it is that, in the most tense moments, image quality is reduced and sometimes in a serious way.
This mainly affects accidents where many participants are involved, when continuous image quality is no longer valid.
The audio is fine and the soundtrack is a matter of tastes.
In order to please most of the youth group, the soundtrack belongs to the category "each of his father and his mother", but it can be assumed that no one would buy the game just for his music.
The final feeling of Need for Speed: The Run is therefore quite confusing.
If the game avoided absolutely silly mistakes, we would have trouble claiming that The Run is the best NFS game in recent years.
It gives the feeling that the game is not finished.
The fun is assured, but prepared because the mistakes will hit you in the eyes with the force of some airport reflectors.
The choirs of the Carolina University will participate in the concert "Terciopel Students".
The joint celebration of the International Day of Students and the anniversary of the Revolution of Terciopelo as a musical experience will take place for the third time at the Festival Academic Festival.
During the same period, twenty corals will be presented from secondary and university centres.
The festival revolves around two concerts on 17 November.
"The Carolina University has a high participation in the festival."
