The new leader eclipsed the founder of IBM ( Watson's ideas remain the firm foundation on which corporate culture and identity are based).
Watson directed the company until 1952.
IBM, as its name indicates, began with the production and sale of all kinds of business equipment, from meat cutters and cheese to register boxes.
