How to detect a lie
A look at the most recent headlines tells us how serious and omnipresent deception and lies are in daily life.
Republican presidential candidate Herman Cain is busy exchanging allegations of sexual harassment with several women; each party accuses of lying to the other.
The administrators of the State University of Pennsylvania have been charged with perjury for allegedly concealing reports that a retired football coach was sexually assaulting children.
