Replacing analog signals with digital signals is one of the most important changes the world has experienced in recent years
The Supreme Court of Justice of the Nation (SCJN) rejected the constitutional disputes brought by the Senate and the Chamber of Deputies against the presidential decree advancing the so-called "analogue blackout" from 2021 to 2015, not meeting the eight votes necessary to invalidate it.
