In favour of the project, only Zaldívar, Jorge Mario Pardo, Margarita Luna and the Sánchez Cordero themselves voted.
With this argument, both the Senate and the Chamber of Deputies promoted two constitutional disputes to challenge the decree, and by admitting the demands, Minister Sánchez Cordero suspended the implementation of the decree and all the actions in it arranged for the digital transition.
