Paris seems to come to a similar conclusion.
The investigation into the kidnapping of two Frenchmen in Niger last January would have resumed the gateways.
Kidnapped in a restaurant in Niamey by persons related to Aqmi, Antoine de Léocour and Vincent Delory died the next day along with several of his kidnappers during an operation launched by the French special forces.
In the rubble of the intervention, French and Nigerian researchers discovered several telephone chips belonging to terrorists.
Terrorist axis
The study of the calls made indicates to several interlocutors based on Mali, Niger and Nigeria.
According to Radio France Internationale (RFI), two numbers particularly captured the interest of researchers: one leads to a Nigerian who stayed for a long time in Maiduguri, a city in northern Nigeria, Boko Haram's sister-in-law, and the other to a man who is supposedly close to Aqmi and the sect.
"It is progress, but we must certainly expect to have more formal evidence before talking about operational cooperation between Aqmi and Boko Haram."
